<DESC><![CDATA[The World Assembly,

Noting the purpose of GAR #546 to lift restrictions upon minority groups from donating blood, while increasing the efficiency of blood donation to improve medical treatment,

However, displeased by these flaws in the resolution&#39;s execution:
[list][*]The target&#39;s failure to effectively prevent discrimination in blood donation, as while it requires that members of minorities be allowed to donate, it still allows the immediate discarding of a minority donor&#39;s blood due to the donor belonging to said minority group.


[*]Section 4 declaring categorically that &quot;it shall be considered a criminal offense to knowingly attempt to donate unsafe blood&quot; includes donation for research, where it is irrelevant whether the blood is safe for transfusions or not. This pointlessly hinders research regarding blood-borne illnesses by making it difficult to obtain blood carrying those illnesses.


[*]Section 5, which states, &#147;existing scientific committees created by this body shall be utilized to share information related to blood-borne illnesses and blood donation across member states, as to mitigate any risk of contaminated blood&#148;, does not include any restrictions or prevention of the sharing of private information of individuals that may possess a blood borne illness, thus infringing on the right of any person to not have their private information disclosed. 
 

[*]The target is largely superfluous under existing laws and does not require replacement. GAR #546 states nearly identical principles to [url=https://www.nationstates.net/page=WA_past_resolution/id=457/council=1]GAR #457[/url], which already addresses discrimination based on sexuality, implicitly including blood donation. Likewise, [url=https://www.nationstates.net/page=WA_past_resolution/id=217/council=1]GAR #217[/url] already declares that &#147;prospective donors of biomedical tissues shall not be discriminated against without a valid medical rationale&#148;.[/list]
Asserting that this repeal will relieve unnecessary burdens upon member states, noting that similar resolutions can function without needing to be duplicated &#150; often ineffectively &#150; by the target,

Hereby repeals GAR #546, [url=https://www.nationstates.net/page=WA_past_resolution/id=546/council=1]Blood Donation Safety and Equality Act[/url]&#148;.

]]></DESC>
